Package com.coinroster

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClassFinder
    ClassFinder: takes a package path and tries to find a class that matches it
    CommandPrompt
    Source code for the CoinRoster command prompt that is used to communicate with the active server.
    ContestMethods
    Methods that create new contests or check the status of existing ones to perform operations.
    CronDriver
    Spawns CronThreads
    CronThread
    New Cron thread used for a CronWorker This is where task timeouts happen if Cron workers fail to return by the timeout interval.
    CronWorker
    Main Cron process handler.
    DB
    Anything to do with standardized database queries go here.
    HttpRequest
    Represents a HTTP request object
    HttpResponse
    Represents a HTTP response object.
    MethodCall
    API middleware.
    MethodInstance
    Represents a method that is passed through API middleware.
    ReferralRedirect
    Redirect after referral.
    Server
    This is the main server object whose implementation calls all threads/crons that start all CoinRoster processes.
    ServerThread
    New Server thread used for a server thread This is where task timeouts happen if workers fail to return by the timeout interval.
    ServerWorker
    Server Worker that accepts and serves HTTP requests.
    Session
    Represents a session between a user on their browser and the server.
    SSI
    Defines Server-Side Includes (SSI).
    StaticAsset
    Handles access to static assets (img etc.)
    Utils
    Common resources used by all classes.
